Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.60,0:00:05.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.98,0:00:09.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Having the cameraman be the\Nseventh person was entertaining,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.27,0:00:13.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and the scene when all of the characters look\Ninto the camera at once did have a lot of impact.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.95,0:00:15.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.61,0:00:18.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The rope didn't feature in it\Nthat way at all, did it?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.58,0:00:25.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,W-Well, nothing's to say that\Nthe rope was part of the setup...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.83,0:00:30.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If that's so, then why was\NHongo-{\i1}senpai {\i0}so adamant about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.00,0:00:32.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's because it was critical\Nto the plot, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.93,0:00:37.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Still, I could be wrong about that, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.10,0:00:41.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyhow, I was entertained\Nby that idea of yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.52,0:00:43.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That finale took me by surprise.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.18,0:00:47.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I just didn't think the twist\Nfit in with the rest of the story.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.31,0:00:49.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.82,0:00:53.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I have to get to my Manga Club.\NSee you tomorrow, Oreki.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.95,0:01:04.37,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I scowled at the wind blowing\Nat my window of boredom{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.37,0:01:12.42,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}so I could turn away\Nthe awkwardness I was feeling{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.76,0:01:20.60,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Hyouka
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.60,0:01:26.02,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I nod noncommittally at today\Nas I hold it in my hand{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.02,0:01:31.40,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}projecting myself a little exaggeratedly{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.40,0:01:36.90,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I get the feeling that\Nsomething is about to change{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.90,0:01:41.99,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It's all because of you\Ncalling out to my heart{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.41,0:01:48.87,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Peeking up at cloudy skies,\NI sense what's coming{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.87,0:01:56.84,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Let's reach out our hands\Nwith courage stronger than ever{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.26,0:02:01.85,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Light and shadow are both still far off{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.85,0:02:08.10,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}but even so, we want to know\Nthe reason for this kindness{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.10,0:02:15.53,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Let's go look now, beyond the brilliance\Nthat goes by nobody's name{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.53,0:02:28.00,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}before it all becomes a thing of the past{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.00,0:02:33.46,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Credit Roll of Fools
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.46,0:02:32.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How could I have forgotten about that?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.00,0:02:35.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did I unconsciously ignore it?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.80,0:02:41.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did I distort the problem\Nto make it fit Kaito?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.84,0:02:43.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hotaro...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.10,0:02:46.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hotaro! Hey, hold up!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.85,0:02:47.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hotaro!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.14,0:02:51.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? What's the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.60,0:02:53.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's nothing. Did you want something?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.44,0:02:58.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I kind of wanted to ask\Nyou something. Where's Mayaka?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.03,0:02:59.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She said she was heading to Manga Club.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.15,0:03:03.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, this works out perfectly.\NIt looks like Chitanda-{\i1}san {\i0}left, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.95,0:03:07.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Meaning that this is something you\Ndon't want Ibara or Chitanda to hear.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.25,0:03:11.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, yeah. I didn't want to bring\Nthis up in front of the others.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.92,0:03:13.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, what is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.75,0:03:17.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,About that plot twist... did you mean\Nfor it to be Hongo-{\i1}senpai{\i0}'s idea?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.59,0:03:19.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Or was that just your idea?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.80,0:03:20.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was Hongo's.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.43,0:03:24.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.68,0:03:29.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hotaro, that plot twist was\Nnot Hongo-{\i1}senpai{\i0}'s idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.81,0:03:33.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know what the right answer is,\Nbut I can say that that wasn't it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.73,0:03:36.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You must have something\Nyou're basing that on, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.07,0:03:37.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.86,0:03:43.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's that critical of an\Ninconsistency, and I didn't see it?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.24,0:03:44.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not an inconsistency.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.03,0:03:46.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not lying when I say\NI thought it was good.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.33,0:03:49.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But it wasn't what\NHongo-{\i1}senpai {\i0}was thinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.16,0:03:50.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Meaning what?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.71,0:03:53.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know what a "narrative trick" is?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.63,0:03:57.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A way to fool the reader by the way\Nthe text is presented, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.63,0:03:58.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.80,0:04:01.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Like in the movie, where the killer\Nis actually the cameraman:
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.59,0:04:03.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that was a narrative trick.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.18,0:04:04.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I suppose so.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.80,0:04:08.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hotaro, what books did\Nthe amateur Hongo-{\i1}senpai{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.35,0:04:10.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,use to study how to write a mystery?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.10,0:04:12.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Holmes, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.64,0:04:16.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right. Hongo-{\i1}senpai {\i0}hasn't\Nread anything but Holmes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.31,0:04:17.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now listen, Hotaro...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.98,0:04:21.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Narrative tricks don't exist\Nin the Holmes stories.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.36,0:04:23.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,1887 A Study in Scarlet\N1890 The Sign of Four\N1892 The\NAdventures of Sherlock Holmes
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.36,0:04:23.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,With very few exceptions,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.57,0:04:24.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,1893 The Memoirs of Sherlock Holmes\N1901 The Hound of the Baskervilles\N1905 The Return of Sherlock Holmes
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.57,0:04:26.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,narrative tricks began in Christie's era.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.99,0:04:26.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,1914 The Valley of Fear\N1917 His Last Bow\N1920 The Mysterious\NAffair at Styles
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.24,0:04:27.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,1922 The Secret Adversary\N1923 The Murder on the Links\N1924 The Man\Nin the Brown Suit
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.24,0:04:29.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Which is to say after entering the 20th century.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.66,0:04:29.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,1925 The Secret of Chimneys\N1926 The Murder of Roger\NAckroyd
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.12,0:04:31.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know Hongo-{\i1}senpai{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.29,0:04:35.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I find it hard to imagine that\Nshe's in Christie's league!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.29,0:04:39.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Personally, that movie\Nwas right up my alley.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.38,0:04:41.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If that was your idea,\Nthen I won't say anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.34,0:04:44.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But if you're passing it off\Nas Hongo-{\i1}senpai{\i0}'s idea,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.80,0:04:46.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have no choice but to say you're wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.64,0:04:50.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hold on a second. We don't know\Nwhat Hongo has ever read.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.39,0:04:53.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe she came across that\Nnarrative trick in some other book!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.14,0:04:55.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Or, hell, maybe she saw it in a movie...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.73,0:04:57.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hotaro!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.81,0:04:59.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you really believe that?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.48,0:05:04.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If that's what you believe in\Nyour heart, I'm okay with that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.36,0:05:09.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's all I wanted to say.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.07,0:05:11.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I'll be going now.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.76,0:05:25.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.01,0:05:27.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought you had already left.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.47,0:05:30.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Um, Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0},
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.60,0:05:32.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,there's something I want\Nto talk to you about.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.22,0:05:35.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.15,0:05:44.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You wanted to talk about the movie, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.11,0:05:46.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.49,0:05:48.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You didn't like it, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.11,0:05:50.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not saying that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.74,0:05:54.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't hold back. Ibara and\NSatoshi already talked to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.62,0:05:58.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They say that it wasn't what\NHongo intended. And I...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.71,0:06:00.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,am beginning to think it isn't, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.59,0:06:04.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think it is, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.88,0:06:11.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Would you mind telling me why?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.47,0:06:18.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The day is still young. Why don't\Nwe go for a stroll along the river?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.32,0:06:30.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0}, do you know what it was\Nthat had me curious about all this?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.57,0:06:33.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How the movie was going to\Nend up concluding, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.83,0:06:35.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That was the reason you came.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.54,0:06:41.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No. The truth is, I didn't care\Nhow the movie ended.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.17,0:06:44.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why I thought that your\Nidea was a very good one.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.25,0:06:46.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then what {\i1}were {\i0}you curious about?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.26,0:06:50.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was curious about Hongo-{\i1}san{\i0}, the girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.01,0:06:55.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought this whole affair was\Nunusual, any way you cut it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.85,0:06:58.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't understand why Irisu-{\i1}san {\i0}didn't\Nask someone close to Hongo-{\i1}san{\i0},
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.93,0:07:05.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,someone like maybe Eba-{\i1}san{\i0}, what the\Nsetup of the plot was supposed to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.57,0:07:07.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In order to let Hongo have her rest, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.07,0:07:12.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you have something on\Nyour mind, then speak up.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.66,0:07:18.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think that Hongo-{\i1}san {\i0}had a clear view\Nof her script right up to the end.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.16,0:07:22.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if she had taken ill halfway through,\NI think they could have still asked her.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.92,0:07:25.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And if she really wasn't\Nin any condition for that,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.17,0:07:28.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think that Eba-{\i1}san{\i0}, who says\Nthat she is her good friend,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.13,0:07:31.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,would be so angry that she could not\Nput up with the rest of the class.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.80,0:07:34.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At least enough so that she\Nwouldn't escort us to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.68,0:07:36.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.68,0:07:44.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did Hongo-{\i1}san {\i0}really not tell\Nanyone what her plot setup was?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.52,0:07:50.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you saying that Hongo intended\Nto write the script herself?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.28,0:07:54.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, the Hongo-{\i1}san {\i0}that we heard about\Nwas too faint-hearted for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.32,0:07:57.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think that a girl like that
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.16,0:07:59.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,would have the backbone to\Nkeep her classmates waiting.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.95,0:08:03.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then maybe she wasn't confident\Nabout her conclusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.79,0:08:05.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's something that I considered, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.04,0:08:08.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But the others in her class are fine folks.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.88,0:08:11.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I doubt that they would\Nslam Hongo-{\i1}san{\i0}'s idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.30,0:08:13.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fine folks, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.88,0:08:16.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If that was the conclusion that\NHongo-{\i1}san {\i0}came up with,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.51,0:08:19.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure she would have had the\Nconfidence to tell the others.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.85,0:08:21.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's how good it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.98,0:08:25.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I don't think it {\i1}was {\i0}that,\Nwhich is why she {\i1}couldn't {\i0}tell them.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.06,0:08:28.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And if that's the case, then what was it\Nexactly that pushed Hongo-{\i1}san {\i0}too far?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.77,0:08:31.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's what I wanted to know.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.44,0:08:35.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And I think that the regrets, the screams that\NHongo-{\i1}san{\i0} had about having to stop writing
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.74,0:08:38.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,before she finished it are\Nhidden somewhere inside!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.87,0:08:45.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But the movie we saw didn't\Nanswer that question.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.50,0:08:48.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If it appears that I didn't enjoy it,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.67,0:08:50.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure that's the reason why.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.34,0:08:59.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,While I was trying to discern\Nthe truth about this movie,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.60,0:09:02.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Chitanda was thinking about Hongo.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.48,0:09:04.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What about me?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.48,0:09:08.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I saw the script as a mere literary\Nproblem to be solved, didn't I?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.32,0:09:12.11,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Whodunit Theater
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.94,0:09:12.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The stage setting...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.65,0:09:15.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The featured characters...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.20,0:09:16.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The murder case...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.78,0:09:18.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The setup...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.78,0:09:19.78,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Whodunit Theater
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.33,0:09:24.20,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Whodunit Theater
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.87,0:09:28.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The killer is among you!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.21,0:09:29.96,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Whodunit Theater
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.42,0:09:35.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I never even considered that Hongo's\Nfeelings might be included in the script.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.18,0:09:43.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hell of a detective I was.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.48,0:09:47.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I'm not blaming you\Nor anything, Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.56,0:09:50.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That resolution scene was quite surprising.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.73,0:09:53.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It may not have been what\NHongo-{\i1}san {\i0}was thinking,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.32,0:09:55.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but I do think that it ended up\Nbeing a good ending.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.78,0:10:00.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not as though I was\Nbrought on to be a scriptwriter.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.04,0:10:09.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What I {\i1}did {\i0}do was a bang-up job\Nof getting everything wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.13,0:10:12.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But {\i1}what {\i0}did I get wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.39,0:10:21.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't get my head around it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.68,0:10:23.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No flashes of insight, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.56,0:10:25.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who really cares, anyway?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.85,0:10:29.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're already done shooting it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.81,0:10:32.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However hard I think\Nabout it now, it's academic.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.19,0:10:35.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thinking it through logically is a waste\Nof time, and not energy-conserving.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.20,0:10:40.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Aw, damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.49,0:10:44.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ow...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.04,0:10:52.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe reading a book\Nwill get my mind off of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.30,0:10:57.05,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,The Mysteries of Tarot
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.88,0:10:59.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So Sis has a book like this one?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.85,0:11:04.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's see...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.60,0:11:08.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"The Empress... maternal affection,\Na fertile mind, sensitivity...?"
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.31,0:11:12.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,From what I've seen, that's not\Nat all a match for Irisu.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.11,0:11:14.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, Ibara was "Justice."
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.52,0:11:17.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Equality, righteousness, fairness..."
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.94,0:11:20.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mm-hm, not necessarily wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.78,0:11:22.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Satoshi was "The Magician."
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.03,0:11:25.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Initiative, originality, interest," huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.49,0:11:30.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hm. And Chitanda was "The Fool."
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.66,0:11:34.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Curiosity, impulse to\Naction..." That follows.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.50,0:11:36.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now for me...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.13,0:11:39.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Inner fortitude, fighting\Nspirit, bonds...?"
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.30,0:11:42.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is this? That doesn't\Nfit me at all, does it?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.18,0:11:45.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why would Satoshi pick this for me?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.31,0:11:52.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"'Strength' is represented by a picture of a\Nferocious lion being controlled by a kind woman."
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.60,0:11:57.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Satoshi! No, I am {\i1}not {\i0}controlled by them!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.40,0:12:00.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not Sis, and not Chitanda, and not Irisu!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.45,0:12:07.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe I {\i1}am {\i0}"Strength."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.95,0:12:11.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's quite fascinating.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.21,0:12:14.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is he using the meanings of the Tarot\Nillustrations to imply something about me?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.50,0:12:15.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That would be just like Satoshi.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.54,0:12:18.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not like he changed my viewpoint...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.34,0:12:22.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Change my viewpoint...?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.27,0:12:37.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.27,0:12:39.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's been a little while, hasn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.86,0:12:40.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hi there.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.86,0:12:43.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The movie turned out well, didn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.36,0:12:45.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All because of your help. Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.03,0:12:48.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Listen, this Saturday,\Nwe're having a launch party.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.95,0:12:50.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Won't you join us?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.00,0:12:51.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I won't be going.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.16,0:12:52.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hm?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.79,0:12:57.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Irisu-{\i1}senpai{\i0}, I need to talk to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.96,0:13:02.97,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Shosho {\i0}('Heat's End')\NFor the sunshine easeth,\Nand blue skies begin their withdrawl
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.26,0:13:02.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hyouka
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.97,0:13:04.84,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Tea Room Hifumi
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.84,0:13:06.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,One Yunnan tea.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.39,0:13:10.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,One green tea.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.97,0:13:13.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please enjoy yourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.98,0:13:16.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, what would you like to talk about?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.73,0:13:20.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The last time we had tea here,\Nyou said I had skill, remember?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.73,0:13:21.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Certainly.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.48,0:13:23.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What skill did you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.24,0:13:27.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you going to make me say it?\NThe skill of deduction...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.36,0:13:28.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's not true, is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.41,0:13:33.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wasn't your detective; I was\Nyour mystery writer, wasn't I?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.63,0:13:44.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What gave it away?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.26,0:13:47.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Holmes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.89,0:13:51.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is it okay if I spoil some\Nof the Holmes stories?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.35,0:13:52.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I don't mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.77,0:13:56.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There were some notes tucked away\Nin the novels that Hongo-{\i1}san {\i0}read.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.52,0:13:58.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I copied some of them down on this.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.65,0:14:00.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At first,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.73,0:14:01.90,OS,,0000,0000,0000,,A Scandal in Bohemia\NThe Red-Headed League\NThe Noble Bachelor\NThe Boscombe Valley Mystery\NThe Five Orange Pips\NThe Man With the Twisted Lip
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.73,0:14:04.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought she was picking out ideas that she could use.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.90,0:14:02.94,OS,,0000,0000,0000,,The Blue Carbuncle\NThe Speckled Band\NA Case of Identity\NThe Copper Beeches\NThe Illustrious Client\NThe Blanched Soldier
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.94,0:14:04.11,OS,,0000,0000,0000,,The Mazarin Stone\NThe Three Gables\NThe Sussex Vampire\NThe Three Garridebs\NThor Bridge\NThe Creeping Man\NThe Lion's Mane\NThe Veiled Lodger
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.61,0:14:06.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, I was mistaken.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.07,0:14:08.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,From what Satoshi told me,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.07,0:14:11.87,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,The Red-Headed League\NThe Three\NGarridebs
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.53,0:14:11.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The Red-Haired League {\i0}and\N{\i1}The Three Garridebs {\i0}had the same plot.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.24,0:14:14.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So why did {\i1}Red-Haired\NLeague{\i0} get a triangle,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.70,0:14:16.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and {\i1}Three Garridebs {\i0}get a double-circle?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.50,0:14:19.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I found out from asking Satoshi about their content
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.50,0:14:22.38,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,The Man With the Twisted Lip\NThe Blanched Soldier\NThe Three\NGarridebs
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.92,0:14:22.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that the double-circled stories are\Nones where the characters survive,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.38,0:14:24.63,OS,,0000,0000,0000,,The Noble Bachelor\NThe Five Orange Pips\NThe Speckled Band\NA Case of Identity\NThe Three Gables\NThe Veiled Lodger
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.38,0:14:24.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,while in the ones marked with an X, they die.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.34,0:14:26.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here is my interpretation.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.13,0:14:29.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hongo wasn't taking into\Naccount the plotlines.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.89,0:14:32.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She preferred the happy endings,\Nand disliked the tragedies,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.97,0:14:35.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,particularly the stories where people died.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.06,0:14:39.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Once I thought of it in that way,\Na number of things made more sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.94,0:14:41.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,One was the small amount of blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.81,0:14:44.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Another was the unusual\Noutcome of the questionnaire.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.78,0:14:45.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Outcome of the questionnaire?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.78,0:14:52.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So you managed to come by this, did you?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.78,0:14:53.41,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,No. 31: How to handle violence?\NNo. 32: How many dead bodies?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.83,0:14:55.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They were generous enough\Nto let me borrow it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.79,0:14:57.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, regarding the questionnaire...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.12,0:15:00.21,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,No. 32: How many dead bodies? One... 6 Two... 10 Three...\N3 More
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.12,0:15:01.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Having over 100 people die would be impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.21,0:15:03.63,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,All of them... 2\NA hundred... 1
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.21,0:15:03.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There are\Nonly about 30 people in the class, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.63,0:15:05.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yet it still got one eligible vote.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.13,0:15:06.05,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Three... 3\NIneligible votes... 1
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.13,0:15:08.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So then, what is this\Nineligible vote, here?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.67,0:15:10.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A vote for there being\Nzero dead bodies, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.30,0:15:13.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That was the vote that Hongo cast, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.10,0:15:16.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No one was supposed to die in her script.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.93,0:15:18.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm impressed.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.44,0:15:22.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, her classmates adlibbed\Nand added in violence.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.65,0:15:26.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I heard that Hongo didn't\Ncome to the shoot.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.94,0:15:31.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And most of all, it doesn't say\Nin the script that Kaito died.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.57,0:15:33.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But in the actual film...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.53,0:15:36.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, indeed. That arm was quite well-made.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.74,0:15:38.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's something that Ibara said, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.66,0:15:40.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,From any angle you look\Nat it, Kaito was dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.88,0:15:49.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,From this point on is just what\NI imagine. I don't have any proof.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.38,0:15:52.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But, Senpai, I can't help but say it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.01,0:15:55.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hongo couldn't bring herself to\Ntell her classmates to reshoot it,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.93,0:15:59.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,since it deviated from her script.\NShe was too timid and earnest.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.06,0:16:05.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think that she felt guilty about\Nignoring the questionnaire tally.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.52,0:16:09.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And so, Irisu-{\i1}senpai{\i0},\Nthat's when you stepped in.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.11,0:16:11.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The way things were headed,\NHongo would end up as the villain.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.61,0:16:16.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You set Hongo up to fall ill,\Nleaving the script unfinished.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.66,0:16:20.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You then got your classmates together,\Nand held a deduction meeting.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.37,0:16:25.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But in fact, what it was\Nwas a scriptwriting contest.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.63,0:16:27.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Once you discovered that\Neveryone's script was poor,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.96,0:16:29.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you dragged {\i1}us {\i0}into it, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.51,0:16:35.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No one even... Not even {\i1}I {\i0}realized\Nthat I was doing your writing!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.22,0:16:39.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's because our viewpoint\Nhad been changed by you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.72,0:16:43.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, you swapped my creation\Nfor Hongo's script,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.77,0:16:46.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so that she got off without being hurt.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.61,0:16:48.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.15,0:16:52.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I haven't yet said you were wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.95,0:16:57.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You said something to me, remember?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.87,0:17:00.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That when people are capable\Nand they don't recognize it,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.33,0:17:02.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it's caustic to those who are incapable?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.16,0:17:04.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You have to be kidding, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.79,0:17:08.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't give a damn about the\Nfeelings of those who are incapable.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.54,0:17:11.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All that you look at is the\Nbottom line. Am I wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.34,0:17:13.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is something the matter with that?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.59,0:17:17.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, when you said that I have skill,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.39,0:17:19.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,was that all for Hongo's sake?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.02,0:17:28.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When you said that everyone should be aware\Nof who they were, was that a lie, too?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.59,0:17:53.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I did not mean it sincerely.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.55,0:17:56.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you wish to call it a lie,\Nthat is up to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.10,0:18:06.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am relieved to hear that.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.90,0:18:18.16,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Puppet Show
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.16,0:18:20.41,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Sleuth Theater
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.41,0:18:24.41,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Come, great detectives!!\NCan you solve this mystery?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.92,0:18:33.55,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Mayuko has logged in.\NPlease insert name here has logged in.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.55,0:18:35.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mayuko: Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.92,0:18:38.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mayuko: It's all because\NI made the script like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.64,0:18:41.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please insert name here: It's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.43,0:18:46.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It may not have been the movie\Nyou were hoping for, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.93,0:18:48.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mayuko: That's not true.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.85,0:18:50.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mayuko: What I was hoping for
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.02,0:18:53.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mayuko: was to cheer with\Neveryone when it was done.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.36,0:18:58.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have to say, you really\Nare something else
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.70,0:19:02.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nah, never mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.45,0:19:06.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,M-e-♪ has logged in.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.04,0:19:06.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,M-e-♪ has logged in.\NPlease insert name here has logged in.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.91,0:19:07.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please insert name here: Hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.79,0:19:08.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please insert name here: Hello.\NM-e-♪: Yoo-hoo.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.71,0:19:10.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,M-e-♪: Sounds like it went well.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.58,0:19:12.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please insert name here:\NThanks to you, Senpai.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.67,0:19:13.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please insert name here: However, I
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.42,0:19:15.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please insert name here: think I did\Nsomething inexcusable to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.09,0:19:16.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,♪: Do you really think that?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.97,0:19:22.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please insert name here: It's no use trying to bluff\Nsomeone on the other side of the world, is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.14,0:19:25.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,M-e-♪: Of course not.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.51,0:19:29.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,M-e-♪: So, no lying to someone\Non the other side of the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.15,0:19:32.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Lying, you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.52,0:19:36.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You didn't ask for my help because you\Nwanted to protect the scriptwriter, did you?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.44,0:19:41.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,♪: The whole problem in the first place\Nwas that the script was dull, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.41,0:19:46.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,♪: You wanted to reject a script that fell flat\Nin a way that wouldn't hurt that girl, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.33,0:19:50.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,♪: Well, it doesn't sound like\Nthe dummy caught on, anyhow.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.63,0:19:54.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wasn't in
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.21,0:19:56.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,any position to
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.75,0:19:57.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,let the project
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.55,0:19:58.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,fail
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.51,0:20:02.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wasn't very well in any position\Nto let the project fail.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.22,0:20:11.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Senpai?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.73,0:20:15.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,M-e-♪ has logged out.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.41,0:20:27.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.33,0:20:29.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.29,0:20:35.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"I am curious what kind of script\NHongo-{\i1}san {\i0}thought up," right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.67,0:20:37.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? No, it's not that.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.30,0:20:40.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What then? This isn't like you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.55,0:20:44.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This isn't like me? Yes, you're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.72,0:20:47.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0}, this isn't like you, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.47,0:20:50.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not like me, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.81,0:20:51.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hmph.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.40,0:20:57.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, let me ask, like me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.02,0:21:02.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am curious what kind of script\NHongo-{\i1}san {\i0}thought up.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.36,0:21:03.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0}, please tell me.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.03,0:21:07.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can only imagine,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.33,0:21:11.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but by assuming Kaito isn't dead,\Nit solves the locked-room problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.50,0:21:14.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Konosu is the culprit, and the\Nentry point is the window.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.83,0:21:16.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? But the window was...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.50,0:21:18.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The window in the right-side sitting room.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.79,0:21:20.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There are two of them,\Nso it doesn't matter which.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.34,0:21:23.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Konosu uses the rope to sneak in,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.80,0:21:26.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,chases after Kaito, and knifes him.\NOne blow, not enough to kill him.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.59,0:21:30.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then she uses the rope to climb\Nto the second floor again,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.10,0:21:33.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and meets up with everyone\Nlooking nonchalant.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.52,0:21:34.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's all.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.23,0:21:38.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, that must be why Hongo-{\i1}san\N{\i0}wished Konosu-{\i1}san {\i0}luck.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.36,0:21:42.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? But what about the seventh person\Nthat Hongo-{\i1}san {\i0}was looking for?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.07,0:21:46.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, they turned up, even in\Nthe unfinished version.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.24,0:21:49.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But it was only those first\Nsix who ever appeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.53,0:21:51.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The cast doesn't necessarily\Njust consist of the actors.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.16,0:21:53.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There was a narrator, too, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.95,0:21:56.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, that's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.96,0:22:00.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, why was the door to the room\Nthat Kaito-{\i1}san {\i0}was in locked?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.38,0:22:04.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kaito went to stage left wing\Non his own, and locked the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.88,0:22:06.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why did he do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.13,0:22:09.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Normally, it would be to keep\Nthe culprit from pursuing him,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.01,0:22:09.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but that's probably not it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.10,0:22:11.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.68,0:22:12.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.97,0:22:17.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, it just seems like I understand\NHongo-{\i1}san{\i0}'s feelings a little bit better.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.52,0:22:19.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.19,0:22:22.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Most likely, after Kaito-{\i1}san {\i0}is stabbed,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.69,0:22:26.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,he talks to Konosu-{\i1}san{\i0},\Nand asks her why she stabbed him.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.70,0:22:30.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, to cover for Konosu-{\i1}san{\i0},\Nhe sends her back up,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.49,0:22:34.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,then goes to stage left wing\Non his own, where he collapses.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.33,0:22:41.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? But then, how does he explain\Naway the fact that he is hurt?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.34,0:22:44.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The injury is simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.34,0:22:46.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There was glass scattered around the room.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.67,0:22:48.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, now that you mention it, that's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.26,0:22:52.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He could say that he cut himself\Non the glass when he fell.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.64,0:22:54.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So that's how the story went.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.22,0:22:57.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Though we'll never know\Nwhy Konosu stabs Kaito,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.31,0:23:00.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,nor the reason why Kaito forgives her.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.98,0:23:03.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That will remain a mystery\Nuntil Hongo tells someone.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.36,0:23:06.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess there's no getting\Naround that, is there?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.44,0:23:07.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why would someone stab another?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.90,0:23:10.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why would the person who was\Nstabbed let their attacker go?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.20,0:23:15.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm very curious as to how Hongo-{\i1}san\N{\i0}was trying to depict that.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.54,0:23:17.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By the way...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.75,0:23:18.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.54,0:23:22.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you know anything else\Nabout this whole incident?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.04,0:23:25.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? No, I didn't know anything.\NWhy do you ask?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.84,0:23:29.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You weren't convinced by any of\Nthe other detectives' theories.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.30,0:23:31.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's not the way you usually are.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.64,0:23:34.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Was your empathy for\NHongo the only reason?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.05,0:23:38.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I get you. Well, um...\NPlease don't laugh at this, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.23,0:23:39.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.48,0:23:43.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think that Hongo-{\i1}san {\i0}and I are alike.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.57,0:23:46.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, this is a little embarrassing.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.99,0:23:48.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The truth is,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.32,0:23:52.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't like stories where\Npeople die, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.70,0:23:57.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That {\i1}is {\i0}like you.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.00,0:24:07.92,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Tonight it turns to love{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.92,0:24:11.68,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Meet me in a pleasant dream{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.68,0:24:15.68,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Make sure that you find me, okay?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.68,0:24:21.02,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Our snooze-time date{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.16,0:24:41.25,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The heat of your budding warmth troubles me{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.00,0:24:52.05,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Don't you understand how I feel yet?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.43,0:24:58.93,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}There isn't supposed to be\Nany significance in your glance{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.93,0:25:04.31,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I mean, it's the same one\Nyou give all your friends{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.31,0:25:10.03,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The tiny wishing star fading\Ninto the morning light{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.03,0:25:15.03,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}and the magic it works during the night\N(I wish you would notice){\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.03,0:25:18.08,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Tonight it turns to love{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.08,0:25:21.79,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Meet me in a pleasant dream{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.79,0:25:25.83,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Make sure that you find me, okay?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:25.83,0:25:31.09,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Our snooze-time date{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.84,0:25:43.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next time, "Those Things\NPiled Up Endlessly."
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.01,0:25:43.48,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Those Things Piled Up Endlessly
